author: freep.com
title: News quiz: The Batted Ball, Jim Harbaugh's favorite restaurant, more
text:
MORE Test your knowledge of current sports events of the past week:
(For the most part, there are no right or wrong answers, so everybody scores a 5.)
Why did the NFL say a flag wasn't thrown when a Seahawk batted Calvin Johnson's fumble out of the end zone?
A) It should have been, but the official thought it wasn't intentional, and a judgment call isn't reviewable. Sorry.
B) The refs are out to get the Lions. Everybody knows that.
C) The Lions' offensive line didn't give the official enough time to throw either.
What did Michigan coach Jim Harbaugh say he loves about Cracker Barrel?
A) The country store.
B) The games: the jumbo checkers and that one with the golf tees.
C) Breakfast.
D) His new buddy Derek Jeter told him that's where he takes all his actress and supermodel girlfriends for those special intimate dinner dates.
Which feud would you most like to see settled in the octagon?
A) Ronda Rousey and Justin Bieber.
B) The Grizzlies' Matt Barnes and Knicks coach Derek Fisher.
C) The Pirates' Sean Rodriguez and that dugout Gatorade cooler.
D) Stephen A. Smith and Kevin Durant.
What controversial NFL player used a poor choice of words?
A) The Cowboys' Greg Hardy said he wanted to come out with "guns a' blazin'."
B) The Patriots' Tom Brady said he wanted to "air it out."
C) The Seahawks' K.J. Wright said he wanted to "tap out."
D) The Dolphins' Ndamukong Suh said he wanted to "kick somebody's helmet off."
What did stoic Jim Caldwell say about the noncall that cost the Lions in Seattle?
A) "Humans make illogical decisions."
B) "That is a human emotion with which I am totally
unfamiliar. How could I be 'unhappy?' "
C) "I am well aware of human characteristics ... but I've trained myself to put up with practically anything."
D) "Live long and prosper."
